ltale signs of the remastered disc versus the original crappy transfer. For example, most people tell you the packaging for the new version has a yellow UPC....not always true. Other people tell you the copyright on the back bottom right of the box says 2010 DW Studios LLC instead of the original which says 2009, also not always true.It seems the only definitive way to tell if you have the new version is to look at the innermost rings on the underside of Disc One itself. Hold it up to the light, and at the end of a string of letters and numbers, you should see \"B1R2\". If you have anything else (i.e. B1R1), you have the original version and NOT the remastered one!If so, exchange it promptly.", :rating=>4.0, :percentage=>80.0, :useful=>[481, 492], :date=>" 2011 January 19", :title=>"How to definitively know you got the remastered version", :location=>"(New Jersey, USA)", :username=>"Lee Dorry", :source=>{:vendor=>"amazon", :url=>"http://www.amazon.com/Gladiator-Signature-Selection-Two-Disc-Collectors/product-reviews/B00003CXE7"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"Pay very careful attention when trying to determine which disc you actually received from Amazon.", :clean_text=>"pay very careful attention when trying to determine which disc you actually received from amazon", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.395, :corrected_average=>0.37, :scores=>[0.1, 0.42, 0.67, 0.39], :total=>1.58, :weighted_total=>1.58}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>1, :text=>"There's conflicting information on the internet as far as the telltale signs of the remastered disc versus the original crappy transfer.", :clean_text=>"theres conflicting information on the internet as far as the telltale signs of the remastered disc versus the original crappy transfer", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.5725, :corrected_average=>-0.24, :scores=>[-0.2, -0.42, -1.335, -0.335], :total=>-2.29, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[],