:emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>17, :text=>"His Emperor Commodus isn't a good villain and has no real character, but Phoenix adds so many layers to him and turns him into a great antagonist that that alone makes his performance excellent.", :clean_text=>"his emperor commodus isnt a good villain and has no real character but phoenix adds so many layers to him and turns him into a great antagonist that that alone makes his performance excellent", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.6975, :corrected_average=>0.41, :scores=>[0.6, 0.42, 0.615, 1.155], :total=>2.79, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{:plot=>25, :cast=>45}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Joaquin Phoenix"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>18, :text=>"He commands attention just as Crowe does.", :clean_text=>"he commands attention just as crowe does", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.29125, :corrected_average=>0.07, :scores=>[0.0, 0.0, 0.895, 0.27], :total=>1.165, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Joaquin Phoenix"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>19, :text=>"All by himself (no help from any great dialogue or development), he creates a villain that is prissy, whining, ambitious, pathetic, and malevolent, and worthy of our hate as well as our pity.", :clean_text=>"all by himself no help from any great dialogue or development he creates a villain that is prissy whining ambitious and malevolent and worthy of our hate as well as our pity", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.11625, :corrected_average=>-0.14, :scores=>[0.1, -0.28, -0.015, -0.27], :total=>-0.465, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Joaquin Phoenix"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>20, :text=>"It's a wonderful transformation.", :clean_text=>"its a wonderful transformation", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.355, :corrected_average=>0.42, :scores=>[0.4, 0.83, -0.25, 0.44], :total=>1.42, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>21, :text=>"To sum it up, the characters themselves aren't really developed at all- but the acting is so good that it seems they are.Now, onto the action, which, as I had hoped, is plentiful and intense.", :clean_text=>"to sum it up the characters themselves arent really developed at all but the acting is so good that it seems they arenow onto the action which as i had hoped is plentiful and intense", :sentiment=>{:average=>1.05, :corrected_average=>0.62, :scores=>[0.4, 0.63, 1.71, 1.46], :total=>4.2, :weighted_total=>4.2}, :context_tags=>{:plot=>25, :cast=>50}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>22, :text=>"It has diversity and grandeur.", :clean_text=>"it has diversity and grandeur", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.145, :corrected_average=>-0.06, :scores=>[0.0, 0.83, -0.125, -0.125], :total=>0.58, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>23, :text=>"All the fights were fast, hard-hitting, uncensored, and very bloody, which is what they should've been like.", :clean_text=>"all the fights were fast hardhitting uncensored and very bloody which is what they shouldve been like", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.0825, :corrected_average=>0.02, :scores=>[-0.1, -0.42, 0.235, -0.045], :total=>-0.33, :weighted_total=>-0.33}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>24, :text=>"And every single fight sequence is unique from the others.", :clean_text=>"and every single fight sequence is unique from the others", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.245, :corrected_average=>-0.14, :scores=>[-0.1, -0.42, -0.25, -0.21], :total=>-0.98, :weighted_total=>-0.98}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>25, :text=>"There's the match where two men fought chained to each other, the opening war battle, Maximus vs. numerous other fighters, and the final sword duel, to name a few. This is so much more than just two half-naked men fighting with swords, which is what it could've been.", :clean_text=>"theres the match where two men fought chained to each other the opening war battle maximus vs numerous other fighters and the final sword duel to name a few this is so much more than just two halfnaked men fighting with swords which is what it couldve been", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.45999999999999996, :corrected_average=>-0.2, :scores=>[-0.3, -0.14, -1.045, -0.355], :total=>-1.8399999999999999, :weighted_total=>-3.6799999999999997}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>26, :text=>"The film also captures the feel and the motion of combat.", :clean_text=>"the film also captures the feel and the motion of combat", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.11875, :corrected_average=>-0.06, :scores=>[-0.1, 0.0, -0.25, -0.125], :total=>-0.475, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>27, :text=>"Ridley Scott speeds up the film slightly during fight scenes to show the chaos and rapid reflexes necessary to survive.", :clean_text=>"ridley scott speeds up the film slightly during fight scenes to show the chaos and rapid reflexes necessary to survive", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.05499999999999999, :corrected_average=>-0.21, :scores=>[-0.3, -0.42, -0.125, 0.625], :total=>-0.21999999999999997, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Ridley Scott"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>28, :text=>"During the fight scenes, the camerawork is nonstop and covers the combat as one big blur to the fighters.", :clean_text=>"during the fight scenes the camerawork is nonstop and covers the combat as one big blur to the fighters", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.3175, :corrected_average=>-0.16, :scores=>[-0.1, -0.42, -0.625, -0.125], :total=>-1.27, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>29, :text=>"(But we can still follow the fights themselves.", :clean_text=>"but we can still follow the fights themselves", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.0037499999999999895, :corrected_average=>0.1, :scores=>[0.0, -0.42, 0.265, 0.14], :total=>-0.014999999999999958, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>30, :text=>")This film also stands out in my mind as one of the most visual, image-driven action films I've ever seen.", :clean_text=>"this film also stands out in my mind as one of the most visual imagedriven action films ive ever seen", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.2625, :corrected_average=>-0.11, :scores=>[0.0, 0.0, -0.61, -0.44], :total=>-1.05, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{:vision=>100}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>31, :text=>"Thanks to Ridley Scott, practically every scene is jammed with wonderful detail, art direction, even distinct lighting (the Collosseum orange, other parts of Rome dark blue).", :clean_text=>"thanks to ridley scott practically every scene is jammed with wonderful detail art direction even distinct lighting the collosseum orange other parts of rome dark blue", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.04624999999999999, :corrected_average=>0.2, :scores=>[0.6, 0.17, -0.99, 0.035], :total=>-0.18499999999999997, :weighted_total=>-0.18499999999999997}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Ridley Scott"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>32, :text=>"Just look at the wide multitude (seemingly infinite number) of battle masks, weapons, and locales.", :clean_text=>"just look at the wide multitude seemingly infinite number of battle masks weapons and locales", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.08250000000000002, :corrected_average=>-0.19, :scores=>[-0.1, 0.42, -0.48, -0.17], :total=>-0.33000000000000007, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>33, :text=>"Cinematography is skillful and impressive.", :clean_text=>" is skillful and impressive", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.2875, :corrected_average=>0.27, :scores=>[0.3, 0.42, 0.065, 0.365], :total=>1.15, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>34, :text=>"There are tons of memorable shots, like Maximus entering the ring with rose petals coming down on him like rain from above, Commodus' pure white battle costume (when he's being risen up on the platform he looks like a demented angel ascending to heaven), and the images used to represent Crowe's home- the gentle hand carressing the wheat reeds, the door to his house, etc.", :clean_text=>"there are tons of memorable shots like maximus entering the ring with rose petals coming down on him like rain from above commodus pure white battle costume when hes being risen up on the platform he looks like a demented angel ascending to heaven and the images used to represent crowes home the gentle hand carressing the wheat reeds the door to his house etc", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.23625, :corrected_average=>0.34, :scores=>[0.7, 0.42, 0.225, -0.4], :total=>0.945, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>["Joaquin Phoenix"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>35, :text=>"They had a surreal quality and each were bathed in their own distinct color.", :clean_text=>"they had a surreal quality and each were bathed in their own distinct color", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.13124999999999998, :corrected_average=>0.03, :scores=>[0.0, 0.42, -0.09, 0.195], :total=>0.5249999999999999, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{:vision=>90}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>36, :text=>"Excellent work, Ridley.A very impressive film.", :clean_text=>"excellent work ridleya very impressive film", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.58125, :corrected_average=>0.48, :scores=>[0.6, 0.63, 0.39, 0.705], :total=>2.325, :weighted_total=>2.325}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>37, :text=>"So why can't all summer movies be this good?", :clean_text=>"so why cant all summer movies be this good", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.48, :corrected_average=>0.41, :scores=>[0.3, 0.42, 0.6, 0.6], :total=>1.92, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>38, :text=>"We'd be spoiled.", :clean_text=>"wed be spoiled", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.3225, :corrected_average=>-0.12, :scores=>[0.0, -0.83, -0.23, -0.23], :total=>-1.29, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:content=>"What a disappointment for such a heralded and popular film.This disc is a retread of the 2000 transfer, made for the DVD.  What this means is that considerable edge enhancement (EE), or false sharpness, remains in place.  Universal, in prepping the old, outdated transfer for release, smeared what is called \"digital noise reduction,\" or DNR, all over the picture, to remove both the natural film grain that provides facial detail and other wonderful Blu-ray things, as well as cover up the nasty results of EE, which include white halos around most edges.The result?  A terrible picture:1. The detail that justifies a Blu-ray upgrade, namely clear backgrounds and great facial detail, is GONE.  It does NOT look like film, and barely upgrades the detail on the DVD.  Yes, it's slightly better, but only because of the increased resolution.  It's a barely noticeable upgrade.2. Some elements are actually missing!  Like arrows and catapult ammunition.  Gone.  Erased.  Some spears have been magically segmented due to the errors.In short, DO NOT BUY THIS BLU-RAY.  It is a mere marginal upgrade from the DVD, and you should send a message to Paramount with your wallet.  This is not worthy of the Sapphire label, and is not worthy of your purchase.", :rating=>1.0, :percentage=>20.0, :useful=>[65, 76], :date=>" 2009 August 31", :title=>"DO NOT BUY THIS BLU-RAY!!!", :location=>