ment=>{:average=>0.315, :corrected_average=>0.29, :scores=>[0.4, 0.42, 0.09, 0.35], :total=>1.26, :weighted_total=>1.26}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>3.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>26, :text=>"Now, that transfer was state of the art for its day, and it was approved by director Ridley Scott, but obviously it's a far cry from the quality of new HD transfers done today, in 2009.", :clean_text=>"now that transfer was state of the art for its day and it was approved by director ridley scott but obviously its a far cry from the quality of new hd transfers done today in ", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.12874999999999998, :corrected_average=>0.13, :scores=>[0.1, 0.0, 0.235, 0.18], :total=>0.5149999999999999, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>["Ridley Scott"], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>27, :text=>"One of the biggest problems is that until fairly recently, video mastering engineers were still applying edge-enhancement to their digital masters knowing that they were going to be used ultimately for standard-definition DVD release, and also analog VHS and laserdisc.", :clean_text=>"one of the biggest problems is that until fairly recently video mastering engineers were still applying edgeenhancement to their digital masters knowing that they were going to be used ultimately for standarddefinition dvd release and also analog vhs and laserdisc", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.065, :corrected_average=>-0.02, :scores=>[-0.2, 0.28, -0.175, 0.355], :total=>0.26, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>28, :text=>"It took the mastering community a long time to break the habit.", :clean_text=>"it took the mastering community a long time to break the habit", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.09, :corrected_average=>-0.07, :scores=>[0.0, -0.14, -0.125, 0.625], :total=>0.36, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>29, :text=>"In this Gladiator transfer, you can see it in the image.", :clean_text=>"in this gladiator transfer you can see it in the image", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.0725, :corrected_average=>0.04, :scores=>[0.0, 0.0, 0.145, 0.145], :total=>0.29, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>30, :text=>"It's also clear that the 2000 digital master has been digitally-filtered to reduce the haloing and other artifacts - the signs of DNR are not hard to miss.", :clean_text=>"its also clear that the digital master has been digitallyfiltered to reduce the haloing and other artifacts the signs of dnr are not hard to miss", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.4125, :corrected_average=>-0.08, :scores=>[-0.2, 0.1, -1.315, -0.235], :total=>-1.65, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>31, :text=>"That's in contrast to the extended edition scenes, which were transferred in HD in 2005 and so look much better.", :clean_text=>"thats in contrast to the extended edition scenes which were transferred in hd in and so look much better", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.20750000000000002, :corrected_average=>0.1, :scores=>[0.2, 0.0, 0.19, 0.44], :total=>0.8300000000000001, :weighted_total=>0.8300000000000001}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>32, :text=>"They're still not quite up to today's standards, but they look far superior to the rest of the film and there's no edge-enhancement or obvious filtering visible.", :clean_text=>"theyre still not quite up to todays standards but they look far superior to the rest of the film and theres no edgeenhancement or obvious filtering visible", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.05000000000000001, :corrected_average=>0.15, :scores=>[0.1, 0.42, -0.41, 0.09], :total=>0.20000000000000004, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>33, :text=>"The footage simply looks natural - as it should.", :clean_text=>"the footage simply looks natural as it should", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.05625, :corrected_average=>-0.01, :scores=>[0.1, 0.0, -0.125, 0.25], :total=>0.225, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>34, :text=>"There's been some talk of DNR being so excessive that - for example - arrows and fireballs disappear from one frame to the next.", :clean_text=>"theres been some talk of dnr being so excessive that for example arrows and fireballs disappear from one frame to the next", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.275, :corrected_average=>-0.1, :scores=>[-0.1, 0.0, -0.72, -0.28], :total=>-1.1, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>35, :text=>"This IS an issue, but the fact is that when you watch the image in full motion it's not something you really notice.", :clean_text=>"this is an issue but the fact is that when you watch the image in full motion its not something you really notice", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.1225, :corrected_average=>0.04, :scores=>[0.0, 0.0, 0.32, 0.17], :total=>0.49, :weighted_total=>0.49}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>36, :text=>"The arrow or fireball is highly visible in one frame, less so in the next, more so in the third, etc.", :clean_text=>"the arrow or fireball is highly visible in one frame less so in the next more so in the third etc", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.14125, :corrected_average=>0.05, :scores=>[0.0, 0.0, 0.19, 0.375], :total=>0.565, :weighted_total=>1.13}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>37, :text=>"You still detect the object in motion, so you don't go, \"Oh my god, that fireball just disappeared!", :clean_text=>"you still detect the object in motion so you dont go oh my god that fireball just disappeared", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.12, :corrected_average=>0.09, :scores=>[0.0, -0.83, -0.045, 0.395], :total=>-0.48, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>38, :text=>"\" The image just looks generally digital and lacking in fine detail.", :clean_text=>"the image just looks generally digital and lacking in fine detail", :sentiment=>{:average=>-0.051250000000000004, :corrected_average=>0.11, :scores=>[0.2, -0.63, 0.3, -0.075], :total=>-0.20500000000000002, :weighted_total=>-0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>39, :text=>"Overall, I would grade the A/V quality of the Gladiator Blu-ray thusly:GladiatorVideo: 15.5 (theatrical footage)/17 (extended scenes)Audio: 18Let me be clear: Gladiator on Blu-ray is quite watchable - especially if you have a smaller screen.", :clean_text=>"overall i would grade the av quality of the gladiator bluray thuslygladiatorvideo theatrical footage extended scenesaudio let me be clear gladiator on bluray is quite watchable especially if you have a smaller screen", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.19875, :corrected_average=>0.22, :scores=>[0.1, 0.42, -0.09, 0.365], :total=>0.795, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{:vision=>70}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>40, :text=>"On the comparative grading scale we use for Blu-ray, the very best DVD video and audio quality would be graded a 10.", :clean_text=>"on the comparative grading scale we use for bluray the very best dvd video and audio quality would be graded a ", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.5549999999999999, :corrected_average=>0.55, :scores=>[0.3, 0.0, 1.085, 0.835], :total=>2.2199999999999998, :weighted_total=>2.2199999999999998}, :context_tags=>{:sound=>100}, :emphasis=>2.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>41, :text=>"So it's definitely an improvement over the previous DVD releases.", :clean_text=>"so its definitely an improvement over the previous dvd releases", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.23249999999999998, :corrected_average=>0.23, :scores=>[0.2, 0.0, 0.355, 0.375], :total=>0.9299999999999999, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>1.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>42, :text=>"The problem is, the best Blu-rays - most high-quality titles on the format these days - score in the 18-19 range.", :clean_text=>"the problem is the best blurays most highquality titles on the format these days score in the range", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.17, :corrected_average=>0.28, :scores=>[0.1, -0.42, 0.405, 0.595], :total=>0.68, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{:sound=>10}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}, {:index=>43, :text=>"So while this disc is watchable, that's just not good enough, either for the format as a whole or for most fans and enthusiasts", :clean_text=>"so while this disc is watchable thats just enough either for the format as a whole or for most fans and enthusiasts", :sentiment=>{:average=>0.7375, :corrected_average=>0.79, :scores=>[-0.2, 0.83, 1.3, 1.02], :total=>2.95, :weighted_total=>0.0}, :context_tags=>{}, :emphasis=>0.0, :people_tags=>[], :people_indexes=>[]}]}, {:rating=>1.0, :percentage=>100.0, :useful=>[355, 469], :title=>"Can't be missed!", :username=>"Russell_", :location=>"from Malta", :date=>"12 September 2005", :content=>"\n\"Gladiator\" definitely is a classic film as it combines a simple, but\nmoving, story with beautiful scenery, filming, direction and score \u0096 it\nis truly a \"complete\" movie.I am mostly compelled with the beautiful script which in a way reminds\nme of poetry, though it is still everyday language. I love the acting\nportrayed by the late Oliver Reed and also Richard Harris. Russell\nCrowe, Djimon Housou and Joaquin Phoenix are also superb and the parts\nsuit them perfectly. There are also a number of less \"popular\" artists\nwho also deserve a big \"bravo\". Amongst them I have to mention ex-Mr\nUniverse Ralph Moeller who is mostly used as the comic relief of the\nmovie. In Gladiator we can also the beautiful and popular Maltese TV\nStar and actress Ruth Frendo, who although has a small part, she is\ntotally brilliant and outstanding.Actually I got to IMDb while I was looking for her name on the\ninternet, in fact on IMDb she has some very stunning photos. I was\nlucky to meet Ruth Frendo whilst she was filming in another Maltese\nproduction. Ruth Frendo is not only a gorgeous and talented actress but\nshe is also amazingly intelligent and very down-to-earth. We will\ndefinitely be seeing more of her work in the future... The scenery used for \"Gladiator\" is brilliant \u0096 and the opening battle\nscene is definitely one of my top favorite scenes. The modern camera\ntechnique contrasts sharply to the brutality of the gladiators actions\nand blood shed during the movie; and I love the light contrasts thanks\nto the lenses which most definitely have been used to create a surreal\nfeel to the entire movie.\"Gladiator\" deserves all the awards and great reviews it has received,\nand for those of you who still haven't gone and watched it \u0096 I can\nassure you that it will be well worth your time and money. So go on and\nrent it now!\n*** This review may contain spoilers ****** This review may contain spoilers ***", :source=>{:vendor=>"imdb", :url=>"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0172495/"}, :rescore_review=>[{:index=>0, :text=>"\n\"Gladiator\" definitely is a classic film as it combines a simple, but\nmoving, story with beautiful scenery, filming, direction and score \u0096 it\nis truly a \"complete\" movie.I am mostly compelled with the beautiful script which in a way reminds\nme of poetry, though it is still everyday language.", :clean_text=>"gladiator definitely is a classic film as it combines a simple but moving story with beautiful scenery filming direction and score it is truly a complete moviei am mostly compelled with the beautiful script which in a way reminds me of poet